    slug: "collection-from-riyadh-us-saliheen",
    description: `Collection from Riyadh Us Saliheen is an English translation of one of the most important and widely used compilations of prophetic traditions (ahadith) in Islamic literature. Originally authored by Imam Yahya ibn Sharaf an-Nawawi (631-676 AH), a towering figure in Sunni Islamic scholarship, Riyadh Us Saliheen (The Gardens of the Righteous) has served as a primary source of Islamic guidance for millions of Muslims around the world for over seven centuries. The book's enduring popularity stems from its practical approach to selecting and organizing hadith — Imam Nawawi chose narrations that address the actual situations Muslims encounter in their daily lives, making the book a functional handbook for Islamic living rather than merely an academic reference.

The compilation is structured into chapters and sections that cover virtually every aspect of a Muslim's religious and social life. The book begins with chapters on faith (iman) and knowledge, progresses through the pillars of Islam including prayer, fasting, zakat, and hajj, and then addresses a wide array of topics including good character, family relations, neighborly rights, business ethics, food and drink, clothing, visiting the sick, attending funerals, and the remembrance of Allah (dhikr). Each hadith is presented with its complete chain of narrators where possible, and the translation preserves the meaning of the original Arabic while making it accessible to English-speaking readers. The selection process that Imam Nawawi employed was rigorous — he drew primarily from the two most authentic hadith collections, Sahih Al-Bukhari and Sahih Muslim, supplemented by other reliable sources including Sunan Abu Dawud, Sunan An-Nasa'i, Jami' At-Tirmidhi, and Sunan Ibn Majah.

This English edition of Riyadh Us Saliheen is widely used in English-speaking Muslim communities across the globe. It serves as a textbook in Islamic schools and weekend programs, a reference for imams preparing Friday sermons, a study guide for halaqat (study circles) in mosques and homes, and a personal devotional resource for individual Muslims who want to incorporate more prophetic guidance into their daily routines. The translation has been carefully reviewed to ensure accuracy while maintaining readability, and the book's organizational structure makes it easy to look up specific topics. Many Muslims keep a copy of Riyadh Us Saliheen on their nightstand or in their prayer space, reading a few hadith each day as a way of staying connected to the words and example of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him). The book's comprehensive scope and practical orientation make it one of the first hadith collections recommended to new Muslims and one of the most frequently revisited books by scholars and laypeople alike.`,
    metaDescription: "Collection from Riyadh Us Saliheen is an English translation of Imam Nawawi's renowned hadith compilation. A practical handbook for daily Islamic living."
